The Telegraph - Calcutta : Frontpage
 Wednesday, January 08, 2003 				 Boys death backlash on hospital
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Jan. 7: The emergency ward of the Calcutta Medical College and Hospital was ransacked this evening by a section of its employees following the death of a boy after a painkiller was injected.																								Shiv Kumar Ram (13), whose father Biswanath Ram works in the microbiology department of the medical college, was admitted to the hospital on January 5 after he injured his leg while playing. Hospital sources said he went into a coma this afternoon, half-an-hour after the injection was given.																								Hospital superintendent Kusum Kumar Adhikari announced that an inquiry committee will probe the cause of death and file a report in seven days. But agitated employees demanded a report by tomorrow.																								Shiv Kumar died due to cardio respiratory failure at 5 pm today, Adhikari said. I have ordered an inquiry.																								Biswanath said his son spoke to his relatives in the morning and was normal till the painkiller was injected.																								Restive relatives and a section of the employees, mostly Group-D staff, barged into the emergency ward, burnt records and broke glass doors.
